♪ KEEP THE COLORS IN THE LINES ♪

02:39.160 --> 02:40.890
♪ KEEP THE COLORS IN THE LINES ♪

02:40.900 --> 02:42.930
♪ TAKE FLIGHT ♪

02:42.930 --> 02:45.730
"BLESSING AND BLOOD,"
A STUNNING PIECE OF WORK.

02:45.730 --> 02:46.790
THANK YOU FOR THAT.

02:46.800 --> 02:48.130
IT INCLUDES A HARROWING STORY,

02:48.130 --> 02:50.590
A BIT OF FAMILY FOLKLORE
ABOUT THE BORDELONS

02:50.600 --> 02:52.790
AND THEIR FIGHT TO RETAIN
THEIR FAMILY'S LAND.

02:52.800 --> 02:54.330
YOU'RE REFERRING
TO THE LYNCHING

02:54.330 --> 02:56.460
OF FOUR OF MY ANCESTORS BY
LAND THIEVES AND MURDERERS.

02:56.460 --> 02:59.660
CRIME COMMITTED, ALLEGEDLY,
BY ANCESTORS OF

02:59.660 --> 03:02.260
LOUISIANA'S LANDRY
AND BOUDREAUX FAMILIES.

03:02.260 --> 03:03.860
IT'S NOT FOLKLORE.

03:03.860 --> 03:06.860
IT CAN'T BE PROVEN THROUGH
TRADITIONAL SOURCES.

03:06.860 --> 03:08.260
BUT NOT ALL TRUTHS CAN,

03:08.260 --> 03:10.390
ESPECIALLY ON THESE MATTERS.

03:10.400 --> 03:13.060
I DO, HOWEVER, HAVE PROOF
THAT A DIFFERENT FAMILY LORE

03:13.060 --> 03:17.290
THAT YOU WRITE ABOUT MAY
NOT BE AS TRUE AS YOU THINK.

03:17.300 --> 03:20.260
YOU WRITE THAT YOUR MOTHER
TRUDY'S MATRILINEAL BLOODLINE

03:20.260 --> 03:23.530
ENDS WITH YOU, SHOULD YOU
DECIDE NOT TO HAVE CHILDREN.

03:23.530 --> 03:25.590
I AM THE LAST LIVING FEMALE
RELATED TO MY MOTHER,

03:25.600 --> 03:27.160
TRU BORDELON.

03:27.160 --> 03:30.960
EXCEPT IT TURNS OUT
YOU'RE NOT.

03:30.960 --> 03:33.230
THIS,

03:33.230 --> 03:36.460
THIS IS MARTHA LEBOSSIER.

03:36.460 --> 03:38.730
SHE IS YOUR MOTHER'S
FIRST COUSIN.

03:38.730 --> 03:41.360
♪♪

03:41.360 --> 03:44.090
IS? SHE'S ALIVE?

03:44.100 --> 03:45.430
SHE IS.

03:45.430 --> 03:47.090
LIVES A BIT OFF THE GRID
IN ONE OF THE REMOTE BAYOUS

03:47.100 --> 03:49.130
OUTSIDE OF NEW ORLEANS.

03:49.130 --> 03:51.990
BUT WE MANAGED TO MAKE CONTACT.

03:52.000 --> 03:53.390
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

03:53.400 --> 03:55.330
SHE'S NOT GONNA BE
COMING ON OUR SHOW TODAY,

03:55.330 --> 03:58.290
BUT SHE DID CONFIRM
WHAT OUR RECORDS SHOW.

03:58.300 --> 03:59.690
SHE'S TRUDY'S COUSIN

03:59.700 --> 04:02.190
AND AT ONE TIME THEY
WERE QUITE CLOSE.

04:02.200 --> 04:03.330
ALMOST LIKE SISTERS.

04:03.330 --> 04:07.260
♪♪

04:07.260 --> 04:09.690
NOW, WHAT ARE YOU
THINKING RIGHT NOW?

04:09.700 --> 04:13.260
♪♪

04:13.260 --> 04:18.330
THAT I'VE NEVER BEEN SO
GLAD TO BE PROVEN WRONG.

04:18.330 --> 04:20.590
[ LAUGHS ]

04:20.600 --> 04:22.990
I WASN'T SURE YOU
WOULD TAKE MY CALLS.

04:23.000 --> 04:26.030
I WASN'T SURE EITHER.

04:26.030 --> 04:28.690
AS THE ONLY WOMAN ON
THE ST. THOMAS CITY COUNCIL,

04:28.700 --> 04:32.890
I'VE LEARNED TO SPEAK PLAIN.

04:32.900 --> 04:38.190
I DON'T SEE US WORKING WITH
YOU TO STOP THE HIGHWAY.

04:38.200 --> 04:40.060
YOUR MIND'S ALREADY MADE UP?

04:40.060 --> 04:42.590
HOW DID A HIGHWAY THAT
ST. THOMAS DID WANT

04:42.600 --> 04:45.590
MYSTERIOUSLY END UP
IN ST. JOE,

04:45.600 --> 04:47.930
WHERE YOU CLAIM MOST
PEOPLE DON'T WANT IT?

04:47.930 --> 04:50.730
BECAUSE THE LANDRYS WANT IT.
THAT'S ALL I KNOW RIGHT NOW.

04:50.730 --> 04:53.860
A FEW MONTHS AGO,
YOU WERE THE LANDRYS.

04:53.860 --> 04:58.430
OWNING THEIR SHARES, PROFITING
FROM THEIR DISGUSTING GREED.

04:58.430 --> 05:02.660
BUT BEING DUPLICITOUS
ISN'T NEW FOR YOU, IS IT?

05:02.660 --> 05:04.130
I'VE READ YOUR SISTER'S BOOK.

05:04.130 --> 05:06.060
THAT'S ALL IN THE PAST.

05:06.060 --> 05:07.660
I DIVESTED MY SHARES.

05:07.660 --> 05:08.860
MAYBE.

05:08.860 --> 05:11.060
BUT I'D RATHER BE
BETRAYED BY ONE OF THEM

05:11.060 --> 05:13.960
THAN ONE OF MY OWN.

05:13.960 --> 05:16.890
LOOK, OUR TOWN IS DYING

05:16.900 --> 05:21.030
AND THAT HIGHWAY WAS JOBS,
NEW BUSINESSES, A LIFELINE.

05:21.030 --> 05:23.360
JOYCE, IF WE GET
IT OUT OF ST. JOE,

05:23.360 --> 05:26.430
WE CAN FIGHT TO GET
IT BACK TO ST. THOMAS.

05:26.430 --> 05:29.090
BUT THE PARISHES,
WE HAVE TO WORK TOGETHER

05:29.100 --> 05:32.230
OR WE'LL ALL LOSE.

05:32.230 --> 05:34.090
FIND THE REAL REASON
THE HIGHWAY WAS MOVED

05:34.100 --> 05:36.330
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

05:36.330 --> 05:38.130
THEN MAYBE WE CAN TALK.

05:38.130 --> 05:42.360
♪♪

05:42.360 --> 05:44.360
Man: GET OFF ME!

05:44.360 --> 05:45.660
WHAT THE HELL'S ALL THIS?

05:45.660 --> 05:46.960
NOW, LOOK, I AIN'T DO NOTHING,

05:46.960 --> 05:48.390
SWEAR AFORE GOD
I AIN'T DO NOTHING.

05:48.400 --> 05:49.590
WHAT HAPPENED?

05:49.600 --> 05:51.390
I DIDN'T DO NOTHING!

05:51.400 --> 05:54.090
-WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, HOLD ON.
-THAT'S ENOUGH.

05:54.100 --> 05:56.960
I FOUND 20 BAGS IN YOUR
WORKER'S CAR OVER THERE.

05:56.960 --> 05:58.890
NOW, THIS LOOKS LIKE
INTENT TO SELL METH TO ME.

05:58.900 --> 06:00.560
YEAH, IT LOOKS LIKE
SOME BULLSHIT TO ME.

06:00.560 --> 06:03.430
HE WAS DRIVIN' ROUND, WHAT,
DECIDED TO SEARCH HIS CAR?

06:03.430 --> 06:04.890
NAH, WE GOT AN ANONYMOUS TIP.

06:04.900 --> 06:06.660
OH, YEAH? BEEN A LOT OF
THOSE GOING AROUND.

06:06.660 --> 06:08.090
WELL, THIS IS
A KNOWN GATHERING PLACE

06:08.100 --> 06:09.760
FOR A BUNCHA EX-CONS.

06:09.760 --> 06:11.430
IT'S CALLED A RE-ENTRY PROGRAM

06:11.430 --> 06:12.830
AND IT GOT
MY DADDY'S NAME ON IT.

06:12.830 --> 06:13.890
SAW YOUR LITTLE SIGN
OVER THERE.

06:13.900 --> 06:15.190
-YEAH.
-THAT'S NICE.

06:15.200 --> 06:17.060
I DON'T GIVE A DAMN
WHAT YOU CALL IT.

06:17.060 --> 06:18.260
IF YOU KEEP TALKING
TO ME LIKE THAT,

06:18.260 --> 06:20.990
YOU'RE GONNA END
UP IN THE CAR, BOY.

06:21.000 --> 06:23.690
SO YOU FORGOT I GOT CAMERAS
ALL AROUND THIS PLACE, HUH?

06:23.700 --> 06:25.930
-OH, YEAH, THE CAMERAS.
-YEAH.

06:25.930 --> 06:27.190
YOU BEEN CHECKING
THOSE CAMERAS?

06:27.200 --> 06:29.260
MAKING SURE THEY'RE WORKING?

06:29.260 --> 06:33.560
ALL DAY, EVERYDAY?

06:33.560 --> 06:35.430
THIS IS SETTLED, RALPH ANGEL.

06:35.430 --> 06:36.660
YOU KNOW I WOULDN'T DO THIS.

06:36.660 --> 06:38.030
I KNOW, BENNY.

06:38.030 --> 06:40.060
WE'RE GONNA WORK IT OUT.

06:40.060 --> 06:42.790
MAN, TAKE IT EASY!

06:42.800 --> 06:44.730
[ SIREN WAILING ]

06:44.730 --> 06:45.660
DAMN!

06:45.660 --> 06:51.390
♪♪

06:51.400 --> 06:54.060
NOVA?

06:54.060 --> 06:58.230
♪♪

06:58.230 --> 06:59.890
CALVIN.

06:59.900 --> 07:03.260
♪♪

07:03.260 --> 07:06.330
CALVIN, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING IN PHILLY?

07:06.330 --> 07:08.060
Man: [ CLEARS THROAT ]

07:08.060 --> 07:10.990
SIR, I'LL MEET YOU INSIDE.

07:11.000 --> 07:12.860
♪♪

07:12.860 --> 07:15.930
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

07:15.930 --> 07:17.390
I'M WORKING.

07:17.400 --> 07:19.730
I'M HERE FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS
AND THEN BACK TO BATON ROUGE.

07:19.730 --> 07:21.490
YOU LIVE IN BATON ROUGE NOW?

07:21.500 --> 07:24.460
YEAH, I MOVED THERE
AFTER THE DIVORCE.

07:24.460 --> 07:26.330
I SEE.

07:26.330 --> 07:28.060
I'M SORRY TO HEAR.

07:28.060 --> 07:30.230
DON'T BE.

07:30.230 --> 07:34.160
I'M NOT.

07:34.160 --> 07:37.930
WELL, I'M HERE JUST
FOR A COUPLE DAYS, TOO.

07:37.930 --> 07:38.860
FOR YOUR BOOK?

07:38.860 --> 07:40.130
YOU KNOW ABOUT IT?

07:40.130 --> 07:41.990
'COURSE I KNOW
ABOUT IT, I READ IT.

07:42.000 --> 07:43.090
YOU DID?

07:43.100 --> 07:44.630
CONGRATULATIONS.

07:44.630 --> 07:49.590
IT'S REALLY FANTASTIC,
IT'S BRAVE.

07:49.600 --> 07:51.460
THANK YOU.

07:51.460 --> 07:53.330
NO, THANK YOU.

07:53.330 --> 07:54.930
IT'S NOT EVERY DAY
THE LOVE OF A MAN'S LIFE

07:54.930 --> 07:56.630
WRITES A BOOK
AND TELLS THE WORLD

07:56.630 --> 07:58.230
THAT HE'S THE LOVE OF HERS.

07:58.230 --> 08:01.730
♪♪

08:01.730 --> 08:05.130
I SAID YOU MAY HAVE BEEN

08:05.130 --> 08:07.690
THE LOVE OF MY LIFE.

08:07.700 --> 08:08.690
OKAY.

08:08.700 --> 08:10.960
[ "BLACKOUT"
BY DAHLIA SLEEPS PLAYING ]

08:10.960 --> 08:17.160
♪ WHY DOES IT COME TO
ME IN THE DARKNESS ♪

08:17.160 --> 08:20.130
YOU SHOULD GET IN THERE.

08:20.130 --> 08:23.690
YES, I SHOULD.

08:23.700 --> 08:26.560
DO YOU HAVE TIME
FOR LUNCH TOMORROW?

08:26.560 --> 08:29.830
YEAH, I'LL MAKE TIME.

08:29.830 --> 08:32.960
SAME NUMBER?

08:32.960 --> 08:35.890
♪ JUST COME DANCING
ONE MORE TIME WITH ME ♪

08:35.900 --> 08:38.060
♪ ONE MORE TIME WITH ME ♪

08:38.060 --> 08:40.330
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

08:40.330 --> 08:42.330
SOMETIMES YOU REALLY
DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU GOT

08:42.330 --> 08:44.930
UNTIL IT'S GONE.
-MM-HMM.

08:44.930 --> 08:49.790
IS MR. HOLLYWOOD
STILL AT HIS MOM'S?

08:49.800 --> 08:52.390
HE WENT TO SEE
ABOUT WILLA MAE.

08:52.400 --> 08:56.690
SHE'S STARTING TO
FEEL HER YEARS.

08:56.700 --> 09:00.260
AND I DO WISH THAT HE WAS HERE

09:00.260 --> 09:01.860
TO HANDLE ALL THIS FOOLISHNESS

09:01.860 --> 09:03.930
THAT I DON'T FEEL LIKE
BEING BOTHERED WITH.

09:03.930 --> 09:05.730
COME ON.
I'LL DROP YOU OFF.

09:05.730 --> 09:07.730
ALL RIGHT.

09:07.730 --> 09:12.390
♪♪

09:12.400 --> 09:14.190
[ SWITCH CLICKS ]

09:14.200 --> 09:19.390
♪♪

09:19.400 --> 09:22.460
[ DOOR OPENS, SWITCH CLICKS ]

09:22.460 --> 09:26.730
[ DOOR CLOSES, LOCKS CLICK ]

09:26.730 --> 09:29.860
[ CAR DOORS OPEN, CLOSE ]

09:29.860 --> 09:33.390
[ ENGINE STARTS ]

09:33.400 --> 09:37.930
♪♪

09:37.930 --> 09:41.390
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

09:41.400 --> 09:44.560
♪♪

09:44.560 --> 09:50.330
[ OBJECTS THUD ]

09:50.330 --> 09:55.430
♪♪

10:00.200 --> 10:01.590
SO WHICH ONE DID IT
TO YOU THIS MORNING?

10:01.600 --> 10:02.860
-MY BABY BOY.
-[ LAUGHS ]

10:02.860 --> 10:04.790
KEEPS ME...
[ SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ]

10:04.800 --> 10:09.760
♪♪

10:09.760 --> 10:14.190
OH, MY GOD.

10:14.200 --> 10:16.530
-BABY, CALL 911.
-YES, MA'AM.

10:16.530 --> 10:17.790
[ PHONE BEEPS ]

10:17.800 --> 10:20.260
YEAH, HELLO?
WE HAVE AN EMERGENCY.

10:20.260 --> 10:22.630
WE'RE AT VI'S PRIZED
PIES AND DINER

10:22.630 --> 10:23.890
AND UM, SOMEBODY BROKE IN.

10:23.900 --> 10:25.390
WE NEED THE POLICE.

10:25.400 --> 10:34.960
♪♪

10:34.960 --> 10:36.690
MISS VIOLET.

10:36.700 --> 10:37.890
MAYBE YOU SHOULD CALL
HOLLYWOOD.

10:37.900 --> 10:39.590
♪♪

10:39.600 --> 10:41.790
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

10:41.800 --> 10:49.190
♪♪

10:49.200 --> 10:51.130
NO.

10:51.130 --> 10:53.530
HE'S WITH HIS MAMA.

10:53.530 --> 10:59.260
AND THIS IS NOT THE FIRST WALL
OF SHIT I DIDN'T RUN INTO.

10:59.260 --> 11:02.960
[ TELEPHONE RINGS IN DISTANCE ]

11:02.960 --> 11:05.560
-SHE SEES IT.
-SHE'S LOOKING AT IT.

11:05.560 --> 11:07.660
SHH, BE QUIET.

11:07.660 --> 11:12.330
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

11:12.330 --> 11:16.130
Man: OH, THAT'S PERFECT.
THAT'S PERFECT.

11:16.130 --> 11:20.060
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

11:20.060 --> 11:22.990
[ TRASH CAN OPENS, BOOK THUDS ]

11:23.000 --> 11:25.930
♪♪

11:25.930 --> 11:27.690
GOOD MORNING.

11:27.700 --> 11:30.590
-HI.
-HI.

11:30.600 --> 11:35.260
♪♪

11:35.260 --> 11:36.930
Woman: MORNING.

11:36.930 --> 11:45.590
♪♪

11:45.600 --> 11:53.490
♪♪

11:53.500 --> 11:57.030
[ LINE RINGING ]

11:57.030 --> 11:59.760
This is Ralph Angel.
Can't get to my phone right now.

11:59.760 --> 12:02.130
Leave a message.

12:02.130 --> 12:07.990
♪♪

12:08.000 --> 12:10.130
LET'S SEE.

12:10.130 --> 12:12.460
YES, MISS BORDELON,
I SEE YOUR RESERVATION.

12:12.460 --> 12:15.390
-JUST GIVE ME A MINUTE.
-THANK YOU. I'M MEETING SOMEONE.

12:15.400 --> 12:16.790
HE SHOULD BE HERE SHORTLY.

12:16.800 --> 12:21.330
♪♪

12:21.330 --> 12:24.990
-AM I LATE?
-NO, YOU'RE NOT.

12:25.000 --> 12:26.860
JUST MAKING SURE.

12:26.860 --> 12:28.590
YOU'RE JUGGLING THIS, I KNOW.

12:28.600 --> 12:30.390
YOUR BOSS DIDN'T LOOK
TOO HAPPY YESTERDAY.

12:30.400 --> 12:32.460
NOT MY BOSS, MY CLIENT.

12:32.460 --> 12:33.790
I'D HEARD YOU LEFT THE FORCE,

12:33.800 --> 12:35.360
BUT I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT YOU WERE DOING.

12:35.360 --> 12:37.490
I HAVE A SMALL PRIVATE
SECURITY COMPANY NOW.

12:37.500 --> 12:39.230
SO, LIKE "BODYGUARD"?

12:39.230 --> 12:40.690
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

12:40.700 --> 12:42.790
THAT'S REALLY
IMPRESSIVE, CALVIN.

12:42.800 --> 12:44.390
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW YOU
WERE INTO HAVING A BUSINESS

12:44.400 --> 12:45.490
AND ALL OF THAT.

12:45.500 --> 12:47.360
I DIDN'T EITHER.

12:47.360 --> 12:49.630
I DIDN'T KNOW
A LOT ABOUT MYSELF.

12:49.630 --> 12:50.960
LAST YEAR WAS
A REAL ROLLER COASTER,

12:50.960 --> 12:55.660
BUT ALL IN ALL IT
WAS A GREAT RIDE.

12:55.660 --> 12:57.590
SHALL WE?

12:57.600 --> 13:00.790
♪♪

13:00.800 --> 13:02.130
HERE YOU GO.

13:02.130 --> 13:06.030
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

13:06.030 --> 13:09.130
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:09.130 --> 13:11.590
I'M FINE. [ CHUCKLES ]

13:11.600 --> 13:14.060
MM-HMM.

13:14.060 --> 13:17.790
REALLY, I'M FINE.

13:17.800 --> 13:22.060
-HEY.
-HEY, BABY.

13:22.060 --> 13:23.330
ANYTHING I CAN DO TO HELP?

13:23.330 --> 13:25.730
WELL, ACTUALLY,
YOU COULD GRAB SOME OF THOSE

13:25.730 --> 13:29.590
BIG TRASH BAGS
AND START FILLING 'EM UP.

13:29.600 --> 13:33.430
-OKAY.
-MM-HMM.

13:37.730 --> 13:40.990
RALPH ANGEL WILL BE
HERE AS SOON AS HE CAN.

13:41.000 --> 13:42.130
IS HOLLYWOOD ON HIS WAY?

13:42.130 --> 13:45.790
I'M -- LOOK, I'M GOOD,
YOU KNOW? I'M FINE.

13:45.800 --> 13:49.990
I'M JUST HAPPY WASN'T NOBODY
HERE WHEN IT HAPPENED.

13:50.000 --> 13:51.260
AND NOBODY GET HURT.

13:51.260 --> 13:55.260
♪♪

13:55.260 --> 13:57.590
THE POLICE HAVE A SUSPECT YET?

13:57.600 --> 14:00.190
UH...[ CLEARS THROAT ]

14:00.200 --> 14:02.860
THEY CAME IN,
TOOK A LOT OF PICTURES,

14:02.860 --> 14:04.860
BUT I DON'T SEE THEM
BREAKING NO SWEAT

14:04.860 --> 14:08.930
BECAUSE I DIDN'T HAVE
ANY VIDEO CAMERAS.

14:08.930 --> 14:10.730
I'VE NEVER THOUGHT
I NEEDED 'EM.

14:10.730 --> 14:13.530
OH, AUNT VI, I PROMISE YOU,

14:13.530 --> 14:15.790
THIS WILL NOT STAND.

14:15.800 --> 14:20.060
WE WILL GET TO
THE BOTTOM OF THIS, OKAY?

14:20.060 --> 14:22.590
THANK YOU, BABY.

14:22.600 --> 14:25.730
MY CHARLEY. [ CHUCKLES ]

14:25.730 --> 14:27.660
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED IN HERE?

14:27.660 --> 14:30.260
WELL, GOOD TO SEE
YOU, TOO, CORDELL.

14:30.260 --> 14:33.060
AND, UH, I'M FINE,
THANK YOU FOR ASKING.

14:33.060 --> 14:34.060
OH, I'M SORRY, MISS VI.

14:34.060 --> 14:35.790
-MM-HMM.
-I'M SORRY, VI.

14:35.800 --> 14:38.460
MM.

14:38.460 --> 14:40.390
WHO WOULD DO THIS?

14:40.400 --> 14:41.930
I DON'T KNOW.

14:41.930 --> 14:44.060
GOOD NEWS IS IT'S JUST STUFF

14:44.060 --> 14:47.730
AND I GOT GOOD INSURANCE,
SO WE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

14:47.730 --> 14:48.930
THIS AIN'T THE FIRST
TIME WE'VE SEEN

14:48.930 --> 14:50.530
THIS KINDA THING, RIGHT?

14:50.530 --> 14:52.330
BUT I TELL YOU WHAT
WE'RE NOT GONNA DO

14:52.330 --> 14:55.430
IS LOOK AT THIS MESS ONE
SECOND LONGER THAN WE NEED TO.

14:55.430 --> 14:59.990
-THANK YOU, HON.
-GRAB A BROOM, A MOP.

15:00.000 --> 15:04.890
SOME MORE TRASH BAGS, ANYTHING
YOU FIND TO CLEAN UP WITH.

15:04.900 --> 15:08.530
FIRST CHARLEY'S OFFICE.

15:08.530 --> 15:10.060
NOW BENNY AND AUNT VI!

15:10.060 --> 15:11.190
YOU'RE RIGHT.

15:11.200 --> 15:14.130
THIS ALL FEELS
INTENTIONAL, PERSONAL.

15:14.130 --> 15:15.860
-MM-HMM.
-HYSTERICAL.

15:15.860 --> 15:17.530
IT'S BULLSHIT.

15:17.530 --> 15:21.890
AND THE REASON
I BECAME A LAWYER.

15:21.900 --> 15:25.730
BUT THE GOOD NEWS IS
WE WERE ABLE TO GET YOU OUT.

15:25.730 --> 15:27.390
AND IT'S GONNA TAKE
MORE THAN THAT COP

15:27.400 --> 15:29.060
TO GET YOUR PAROLE REVOKED.

15:29.060 --> 15:33.660
♪♪

15:33.660 --> 15:37.790
I UNDERSTAND IF YOU
DON'T WANNA TALK,

15:37.800 --> 15:39.730
BUT YOU HAVEN'T EATEN
ANYTHING EITHER.

15:39.730 --> 15:47.030
♪♪

15:47.030 --> 15:50.260
WHEN I WAS GROWING UP,

15:50.260 --> 15:51.860
I USED TO THINK IF
I KEPT MY HEAD DOWN,

15:51.860 --> 15:57.360
DIDN'T BOTHER NOBODY,
NOBODY WOULD BOTHER ME.

15:57.360 --> 16:00.390
NOW I KNOW
THAT'S NOT HOW IT IS.

16:00.400 --> 16:04.360
YEAH, IT AIN'T RIGHT
THIS HAPPENING TO YOU,

16:04.360 --> 16:06.790
BUT YOU CAN'T GIVE UP.

16:06.800 --> 16:10.790
I AIN'T GIVING UP.

16:10.800 --> 16:12.860
JUST DON'T KNOW WHERE
I'D BE WITHOUT Y'ALL.

16:12.860 --> 16:16.890
♪♪

16:16.900 --> 16:19.590
IT'LL BE AIGHT.

16:19.600 --> 16:23.590
[ INHALES DEEPLY,
EXHALES SLOWLY ]

16:23.600 --> 16:25.990
IT'LL BE AIGHT.

16:26.000 --> 16:29.360
♪♪

16:29.360 --> 16:30.860
[ PAPERS RUSTLING ]

16:30.860 --> 16:35.330
I HAVE TO SAY, AUNT VI,
YOU ARE HANDLING THIS VERY WELL.

16:35.330 --> 16:37.730
WELL, CRAWLING INTO
THE FETAL POSITION

16:37.730 --> 16:39.860
AIN'T GONNA HELP NONE.

16:39.860 --> 16:44.390
BESIDES, I'VE BEEN
THROUGH THIS BEFORE.

16:44.400 --> 16:47.160
THE DINER'S BEEN
VANDALIZED BEFORE?

16:47.160 --> 16:49.890
NOPE. MY HOUSE.

16:49.900 --> 16:53.130
A PARTING GIFT FROM JIMMY DALE.

16:53.130 --> 16:55.590
I GOT THROUGH THAT.

16:55.600 --> 16:58.330
I'M GONNA GET THROUGH THIS.

16:58.330 --> 16:59.660
WHAT'S HOLLYWOOD SAY?

16:59.660 --> 17:03.790
♪♪

17:03.800 --> 17:04.930
I AIN'T TALKED TO HIM.

17:04.930 --> 17:12.130
♪♪

17:12.130 --> 17:13.460
ARE Y'ALL OKAY?

17:13.460 --> 17:16.660
WE'RE FINE.

17:16.660 --> 17:19.590
I'M THE ONE WITH THE PROBLEM.

17:19.600 --> 17:22.930
SINCE JIMMY DALE SHOWED UP,

17:22.930 --> 17:27.190
CAN'T STAND TO BE
TOUCHED BY THE MAN I LOVE

17:27.200 --> 17:30.860
BECAUSE OF THE MAN I HATE.

17:30.860 --> 17:35.060
DOCTOR THINKS I HAVE PTSD.

17:35.060 --> 17:37.730
PROMISED HOLLYWOOD I WAS
GONNA GET RIGHT WITH MYSELF

17:37.730 --> 17:41.790
BEFORE HE COMES HOME AND...

17:41.800 --> 17:44.790
THIS FOOLISHNESS HAPPENING
TODAY AIN'T GONNA CHANGE THAT.

17:44.800 --> 17:47.790
♪♪

17:47.800 --> 17:49.590
I'M OKAY.

17:49.600 --> 17:52.090
I AM STILL STRONG.

17:52.100 --> 17:53.290
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

17:53.300 --> 17:54.730
COME ON.

17:54.730 --> 17:57.790
[ PHONE CHIMES ]

17:57.800 --> 18:00.190
OH, HEY, BABY.

18:00.200 --> 18:01.990
ANYTHING YOU NEED, AUNT VI.

18:02.000 --> 18:04.460
I GOT YOU.

18:04.460 --> 18:05.930
SORRY.

18:05.930 --> 18:10.460
YEAH, THANK YOU, BABY.

18:10.460 --> 18:13.130
-GOOD, CHARLEY?
-YEAH.

18:13.130 --> 18:14.530
YEAH, YEAH, I WILL BE.

18:14.530 --> 18:16.330
UM...

18:16.330 --> 18:17.530
RA, CAN I SEE YOU FOR A SECOND?

18:17.530 --> 18:21.530
SOMETHING JUST CAME UP.

18:21.530 --> 18:23.390
OH, I'M GOOD.

18:23.400 --> 18:29.260
♪♪

18:29.260 --> 18:31.190
-I LOVE YOU.
-I LOVE YOU MORE.

18:31.200 --> 18:34.260
♪♪

18:34.260 --> 18:38.590
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

18:38.600 --> 18:41.590
THANK YOU
FOR RETURNING MY CALL.

18:41.600 --> 18:42.930
I'M GLAD YOU REACHED OUT.

18:42.930 --> 18:45.530
I'M JUST SICK OVER WHAT
HAPPENED TO VIOLET.

18:45.530 --> 18:47.990
UH...

18:48.000 --> 18:51.790
BUT I HAVE

18:51.800 --> 18:53.990
WHAT I THINK YOU MIGHT NEED.

18:54.000 --> 18:57.660
MY PHARMACY HAS THREE
HIDDEN SECURITY CAMERAS.

18:57.660 --> 18:59.030
GREAT.

18:59.030 --> 19:01.130
BUT WHICH ONE FACES
MY AUNT'S DINER?

19:01.130 --> 19:04.390
THIS GOES BACK
A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

19:04.400 --> 19:05.960
[ CLICKS ]

19:05.960 --> 19:09.330
STOP.

19:09.330 --> 19:11.990
THIS MAN WITH THE CAMERA.

19:12.000 --> 19:15.030
HE LOOKS LIKE HANK MILLER.

19:15.030 --> 19:19.460
WHO'S HANK MILLER?

19:19.460 --> 19:21.390
JACOB BOUDREAUX'S
NEW BUSINESS CONSULTANT.

19:21.400 --> 19:23.730
HE'S A CREEPY GUY,
HE'S ALWAYS LURKING AROUND.

19:23.730 --> 19:25.860
WAIT, UH, GO BACK.

19:25.860 --> 19:27.990
[ CLICKS ]

19:28.000 --> 19:29.660
THERE HE IS AGAIN.

19:29.660 --> 19:33.930
TAKING PICTURES OF AUNT VI'S
DINER ON TWO DIFFERENT DAYS.

19:33.930 --> 19:36.590
♪♪

19:36.600 --> 19:39.330
SO HE'S WATCHING US.

19:39.330 --> 19:41.790
WHY?

19:41.800 --> 19:44.330
[ CLICKS ]
-GOT HIM.

19:44.330 --> 19:45.590
HERE'S YOUR GUY.

19:45.600 --> 19:47.790
RED-HANDED, TOO.

19:47.800 --> 19:53.330
HOLDING A BASEBALL BAT
AND RUNNING FROM THE SHOP.

19:53.330 --> 19:55.730
HEY. [ CLEARS THROAT ]

19:55.730 --> 19:59.590
♪♪

19:59.600 --> 20:02.190
-THAT'S JOAQUIN.
-IGNACIO'S SON?

20:02.200 --> 20:05.130
YEAH, JOAQUIN, IGNACIO'S SON.

20:05.130 --> 20:07.730
I KNOW WE GOTTA HANDLE IT,

20:07.730 --> 20:11.030
BUT HE GOING THROUGH
A LOT RIGHT NOW, CHARLEY.

20:11.030 --> 20:12.590
SOMETHING'S OFF ABOUT THIS.

20:12.600 --> 20:13.860
I MEAN, HIS BROTHER
AND HIS DADDY

20:13.860 --> 20:15.390
PROBABLY GONNA GET DEPORTED.

20:15.400 --> 20:17.390
[ SIGHS ]

20:17.400 --> 20:21.590
WE CAN'T PUT THIS ON HIM.
HIS MAMA?

20:21.600 --> 20:23.330
WE CAN'T TAKE AWAY
ANOTHER KID FROM HER.

20:23.330 --> 20:26.760
♪♪

20:26.760 --> 20:29.490
I KNOW SOMEONE
WHO CAN HELP US.

20:29.500 --> 20:31.130
♪♪

20:31.130 --> 20:34.530
JUST WHEN I THOUGHT YOU
COULDN'T GET ANY STRONGER

20:34.530 --> 20:35.990
OR BRAVER, YOU DO.

20:36.000 --> 20:39.530
I DON'T KNOW
THAT I FEEL BRAVE.

20:39.530 --> 20:42.660
THINGS ARE HARD RIGHT NOW.

20:42.660 --> 20:44.990
MY FAMILY'S
NOT SPEAKING TO ME.

20:45.000 --> 20:47.490
INCLUDING YOUR AUNT VIOLET?

20:47.500 --> 20:49.360
EVEN AUNT VI.

20:49.360 --> 20:52.790
♪♪

20:52.800 --> 20:54.860
SO YOU'RE ON THE ROAD
ALL ALONE?

20:54.860 --> 20:56.860
GOING THROUGH THE WHOLE
SPOTLIGHT STUFF SOLO?

20:56.860 --> 20:59.330
YEAH.

20:59.330 --> 21:02.130
I KEEP SAYING THAT
IT'LL SMOOTH OUT,

21:02.130 --> 21:05.330
THAT IT TAKES TIME
AND THE WOUNDS WILL HEAL,

21:05.330 --> 21:07.260
BUT AS THE WEEKS ARE
TURNING INTO MONTHS

21:07.260 --> 21:08.590
AND NO ONE'S
RETURNING MY CALLS,

21:08.600 --> 21:11.590
I FEEL LIKE...

21:11.600 --> 21:15.160
I MAY HAVE LOST MY FAMILY.

21:15.160 --> 21:18.290
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S POSSIBLE.

21:18.300 --> 21:19.630
THERE'S TOO MUCH LOVE THERE

21:19.630 --> 21:22.860
AND LOVE JUST DOESN'T DISAPPEAR
BECAUSE WE WANT IT TO.

21:22.860 --> 21:28.430
♪♪

21:28.430 --> 21:32.130
CALVIN, I SAID SOME
THINGS IN MY BOOK

21:32.130 --> 21:36.860
ABOUT YOU, ABOUT US,

21:36.860 --> 21:40.060
AND ABOUT HOW I FELT THEN.

21:40.060 --> 21:41.860
HOW DO YOU FEEL NOW?

21:41.860 --> 21:45.460
I DON'T KNOW.

21:45.460 --> 21:48.690
DO YOU?

21:48.700 --> 21:52.490
I DON'T KNOW EITHER.

21:52.500 --> 21:54.660
I THOUGHT I HAD IT
ALL FIGURED OUT,

21:54.660 --> 21:58.930
THAT I HAD TO PUT US
BEHIND ME.

21:58.930 --> 22:00.530
BUT WHEN I SAW YOU YESTERDAY,

22:00.530 --> 22:05.490
THAT WENT RIGHT OUT
THAT WINDOW.

22:05.500 --> 22:10.260
AND MY WORLD
WAS SPINNING ROUND.

22:10.260 --> 22:14.030
ME, TOO.

22:16.300 --> 22:19.060
SO THIS IS YOUR SPOT?

22:19.060 --> 22:22.660
[ SIGHS ]

22:22.660 --> 22:25.260
WHERE YOU RELAX? [ LAUGHS ]

22:25.260 --> 22:28.530
WORKS FOR ME.

22:28.530 --> 22:31.730
I'M TRYING.

22:31.730 --> 22:36.460
YOU DID MORE THAN TRY IT.

22:36.460 --> 22:38.390
LIKE THIS, RIGHT?

22:38.400 --> 22:40.330
SORT OF.

22:40.330 --> 22:44.190
RIGHT.

22:44.200 --> 22:46.060
[ BALLS CLACKING ]
-OH! [ LAUGHS ]

22:46.060 --> 22:48.860
THAT'S YOUR FAULT.
I'M BETTER THAN THAT.

22:48.860 --> 22:52.130
-THAT'S WHAT THEY ALL SAY.
-ALL?

22:52.130 --> 22:54.690
SO I'M NOT THE FIRST WOMAN
THAT YOU BROUGHT HERE?

22:54.700 --> 22:56.230
IT'S LIKE THAT?

22:56.230 --> 22:57.490
NO, NO, NO, IT'S
DEFINITELY NOT LIKE THAT.

22:57.500 --> 22:58.830
MM.

22:58.830 --> 23:01.260
I SPEND A LOT OF TIME
BY MYSELF THESE DAYS.

23:01.260 --> 23:04.130
THINKING OF
THE ONE I LET GET AWAY.

23:04.130 --> 23:07.990
AMONGST OTHER THINGS.

23:08.000 --> 23:09.730
SO WHAT'S NEXT?

23:09.730 --> 23:13.590
♪♪

23:13.600 --> 23:16.530
THIS IS THE BEST DAY
I'VE HAD IN A LONG TIME.

23:16.530 --> 23:18.660
♪♪

23:18.660 --> 23:19.990
THANK YOU.

23:20.000 --> 23:24.390
Woman: ♪ SEE THE TEARS
FALL FROM MY EYES ♪

23:24.400 --> 23:28.030
[ KEYS JANGLING ]

23:28.030 --> 23:30.990
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

23:31.000 --> 23:33.360
THOUGHT YOU WAS
COMING BACK LATER.

23:33.360 --> 23:36.760
ABOUT TO PICK UP BLUE,
GOTTA ROLL.

23:36.760 --> 23:40.690
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU FIRST.

23:40.700 --> 23:42.230
WHAT'S UP?

23:42.230 --> 23:44.090
I'M HEARING
FROM SOME COLLEAGUES

23:44.100 --> 23:47.690
AT PUBLIC SAFETY
AND CORRECTIONS THAT

23:47.700 --> 23:52.190
BENNY'S ARREST IS GIVING
THEM CAUSE FOR CONCERN.

23:52.200 --> 23:55.130
YOUR RE-ENTRY PROGRAM IS
GONNA GO UNDER REVIEW.

23:55.130 --> 23:56.660
-AND SOON.
-THEY GONNA SHUT ME DOWN?

23:56.660 --> 23:58.060
THEY'RE GONNA TRY.

23:58.060 --> 23:59.260
BUT WE'RE NOT GONNA
LET THAT HAPPEN,

23:59.260 --> 24:00.190
NOT WITHOUT A FIGHT.

24:00.200 --> 24:01.460
THEN HOW DO WE STOP IT?

24:01.460 --> 24:04.460
GET WITNESSES ON
THE DAY OF THE ARREST.

24:04.460 --> 24:05.990
THEY'LL GO OVER
RECORDS AND PROTOCOLS

24:06.000 --> 24:08.390
FOR HOW YOU'RE
RUNNING THE PROGRAM.

24:08.400 --> 24:09.730
IF YOU HAVE
SURVEILLANCE TAPES --

24:09.730 --> 24:12.260
YEAH, I DID.

24:12.260 --> 24:13.390
TILL GUIDRY MESSED WITH 'EM.

24:13.400 --> 24:15.190
THEN WE'LL PROVE
HE TAMPERED WITH THEM.

24:15.200 --> 24:18.860
BUT IF I LOSE...

24:18.860 --> 24:21.460
THEY COULD REVOKE YOUR
GRANT FUNDING AND KILL IT.

24:21.460 --> 24:23.860
BUT FIRST THING'S, FIRST.

24:23.860 --> 24:26.960
WE CLEAR BENNY'S NAME.

24:26.960 --> 24:31.390
WE WILL HIT THEM WITH
EVERYTHING WE CAN.

24:31.400 --> 24:34.060
IF THEY'RE GONNA
TAKE THIS FROM YOU,

24:34.060 --> 24:35.790
THEY'RE GONNA HAVE
TO WORK FOR IT.

24:35.800 --> 24:39.660
♪♪

24:39.660 --> 24:41.190
IT MEANS A LOT.

24:41.200 --> 24:43.060
FOR REAL.

24:43.060 --> 24:46.660
APPRECIATE YOU.

24:46.660 --> 24:47.730
YOU MEAN A LOT.

24:47.730 --> 24:55.330
♪♪

24:55.330 --> 25:03.130
♪♪

25:03.130 --> 25:05.230
LET'S GET BLUE.

25:05.230 --> 25:07.590
THANK YOU FOR BRINGING
THIS TO OUR ATTENTION

25:07.600 --> 25:09.260
INSTEAD OF THE POLICE.

25:09.260 --> 25:12.230
[ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

25:30.500 --> 25:32.760
I DIDN'T WANNA DO IT.

25:32.760 --> 25:37.730
THEN THIS MAN
OFFERED ME $500.

25:37.730 --> 25:39.990
I SAID NO.

25:40.000 --> 25:44.330
THEN HE SAID HE'D DO TO
MY MOM WHAT THEY DID TO MY DAD

25:44.330 --> 25:45.990
UNLESS I THREW THAT
BRICK THROUGH YOUR WINDOW

25:46.000 --> 25:50.760
AND MESSED UP THE DINER.

25:50.760 --> 25:53.690
I'M VERY SORRY.

25:53.700 --> 26:00.590
♪♪

26:00.600 --> 26:07.790
♪♪

26:07.800 --> 26:11.590
IS THIS THE MAN
WHO THREATENED YOU?

26:11.600 --> 26:15.860
♪♪

26:15.860 --> 26:20.930
HE WORKS FOR THE LANDRYS.

26:20.930 --> 26:23.930
NO. I KNOW THIS MAN.

26:23.930 --> 26:27.360
I'VE SEEN HIM BEFORE.
NOT THE LANDRYS.

26:27.360 --> 26:29.690
HE WORKS FOR OLD WORLD ENERGY.

26:29.700 --> 26:31.330
THE GAS COMPANY?

26:31.330 --> 26:33.460
HE WAS HANGING OUT AT
MY CHURCH A WHILE AGO,

26:33.460 --> 26:35.930
TRYING TO GET MY PARISHIONERS
TO SELL THEIR LAND TO HIM.

26:35.930 --> 26:37.460
AT LOW-BALL PRICES, TOO.

26:37.460 --> 26:40.730
OLD WORLD ENERGY JUST
DRILLS ALL OVER THE PLACE

26:40.730 --> 26:42.860
FOR NATURAL GAS, SO,

26:42.860 --> 26:44.730
IT'S PROBABLY...

26:44.730 --> 26:45.730
FOR FRACKING.

26:45.730 --> 26:48.030
IN ST. JOE?

26:48.030 --> 26:49.790
WHY WOULD SOMEBODY
FROM A FRACKING COMPANY

26:49.800 --> 26:54.330
BE HANGING AROUND
MY AUNT'S DINER?

26:54.330 --> 26:56.290
EXCUSE ME.

26:59.030 --> 27:02.130
JOAQUIN DID
THE DAMAGE TO THE DINER.

27:02.130 --> 27:04.660
HE THREW THAT BRICK
THROUGH MY WINDOW.

27:04.660 --> 27:07.660
BUT SOMEBODY ELSE PUT
THAT BRICK IN HIS HAND.

27:07.660 --> 27:10.190
AND THAT'S WHO I WANT.

27:10.200 --> 27:12.930
[ BOTTLE THUDS ]

27:12.930 --> 27:19.660
[ ENGINE REVS IN DISTANCE ]

27:19.660 --> 27:21.930
IT'S NOT A POISONED
CHALICE, JACOB.

27:21.930 --> 27:27.530
♪♪

27:27.530 --> 27:32.190
LAST TIME WE SPOKE,
I WAS RUDE.

27:32.200 --> 27:34.190
AND WRONG.

27:34.200 --> 27:37.990
YOU TRIED TO WARN ME,
BUT I DIDN'T LISTEN.

27:38.000 --> 27:41.530
I APOLOGIZE.

27:41.530 --> 27:44.330
I SHOULD BE HELD ACCOUNTABLE.

27:44.330 --> 27:46.990
YOU WERE TRYING TO HELP

27:47.000 --> 27:51.190
AND I PUSH BACK REALLY HARD.

27:51.200 --> 27:54.590
SO HARD IT GOT ME THINKING.

27:54.600 --> 27:57.260
WHAT AM I REALLY
AFRAID OF HERE?

27:57.260 --> 27:58.960
[ LAUGHS ]

27:58.960 --> 28:01.030
[ GLASS THUDS ]
-I'M NOT LAUGHING.

28:01.030 --> 28:04.590
♪♪

28:04.600 --> 28:07.130
WE'RE RUNNING
AGAINST EACH OTHER.

28:07.130 --> 28:08.790
PEOPLE MAKE ALL
KINDS OF ARRANGEMENTS

28:08.800 --> 28:11.930
TO GET WHAT THEY WANT.

28:11.930 --> 28:15.330
OR NEED.

28:15.330 --> 28:19.860
WE BOTH KNOW THAT.

28:19.860 --> 28:22.130
WHAT'S THE CATCH?

28:22.130 --> 28:29.990
♪♪

28:30.000 --> 28:37.560
♪♪

28:37.560 --> 28:41.990
SO, OLD WORLD ENERGY
IS COMING TO ST. JOE.

28:42.000 --> 28:43.790
♪♪

28:43.800 --> 28:46.930
TELL ME ABOUT YOUR DEAL
WITH OLD WORLD ENERGY,

28:46.930 --> 28:48.130
ABOUT HANK MILLER.

28:48.130 --> 28:49.290
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

28:49.300 --> 28:52.060
DRILLING FOR NATURAL GAS,
FRACKING?

28:52.060 --> 28:54.390
I'M TALKING ABOUT
THE PLAN TO TURN ST. JOE

28:54.400 --> 28:56.990
INTO ANOTHER TOXIC GHOST TOWN.

28:57.000 --> 29:00.460
WHAT'S THE HIGHWAY FOR?
TO GET EQUIPMENT IN AND OUT?

29:00.460 --> 29:03.260
♪♪

29:03.260 --> 29:05.690
A NEW HIGHWAY MAKES
NEW INDUSTRY POSSIBLE.

29:05.700 --> 29:07.590
THEY ALWAYS DO.

29:07.600 --> 29:09.330
IT'LL ALSO BRING JOBS,
MONEY --

29:09.330 --> 29:10.730
THAT'S WHAT YOU ALL
SAID ABOUT THE PRISON.

29:10.730 --> 29:11.660
WAS THAT JUST A RUSE?

29:11.660 --> 29:14.060
WHEN WE SURVEYED
FOR THE PRISON,

29:14.060 --> 29:16.390
WE FOUND GAS
DEPOSITS IN ST. JOE.

29:16.400 --> 29:18.460
MY MOTHER TEAMED UP
WITH OLD WORLD ENERGY

29:18.460 --> 29:21.260
TO LOCK DOWN THE LAND.

29:21.260 --> 29:23.290
BETWEEN THE NEW TARIFFS
AND THE TRADE WARS,

29:23.300 --> 29:24.730
